teacup /ˈtiːˌkʌp/

(teacups) 

1. N-COUNT A teacup is a cup that you use for drinking tea. 茶杯 

2. PHRASE If you describe a situation as a storm in a teacup , you think that a lot of fuss is being made about something that is not important. 小题大做 [美国英语] [PHR after v, v-link PHR] 

例： For some, it may seem silly, a storm in a teacup. 对有些人来说，这似乎很荒唐，是小题大做。

